full_text: The statement noted the importance of the consistent and creative application and development of Marxism-Leninism in promoting the cause of Party building and socialism, so as to constantly develop and make efforts for the cause of peace and progress of humanity...

In a joint statement, the two sides agreed that the traditional friendship of being both comrades and brothers, built and cultivated by Ho Chi Minh, Mao Zedong and other senior leaders, is a valuable asset which should be further inherited, protected and promoted well...

Noting China and Vietnam are good neighbors and friends ‚Äúconnected by mountains and rivers, as close as lips and teeth,‚Äù Xi said the two countries are like-minded comrades and partners with a shared future committed to the cause of peace and progress of humanity...

Xi also awarded Nguyen with the Friendship Medal, China‚Äôs highest decoration for foreigners, hailing Trong as a staunch Marxist, close comrade and sincere friend of the CPC. The medal symbolizes the profound friendship between China and Vietnam as ‚Äúcomrades and brothers‚Äù...

Xi called on the CPC and CPV to strive for the happiness of the people and the progress of humanity, advance socialist modernization, and never allow anyone to interfere with their progress or any force to shake the institutional foundation of their development...

Besides diverse areas of bilateral cooperation ‚Äì with 13 cooperation documents signed ‚Äì along with regional and international issues, the visit was notable for the strong emphasis placed by both sides on the importance of their joint commitment to the cause of socialism...

Global Times commented: ‚ÄúThe US in the past few years has tried to rope in Vietnam to join the US strategy to contain China, but Nguyen‚Äôs visit just once again proves that the West has failed to understand and interpret the ties between China and its neighbor‚Äù ...

Besides being the first foreign leader to visit China after the Congress, it was Trong‚Äôs first overseas trip since his re-election in early 2021, reciprocating Xi Jinping‚Äôs first overseas visit being to Hanoi after the CPC‚Äôs 19th Congress in 2017...
